Heat the oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6. Put the @sweet{2} potato in a roasting tin and drizzle over 1½ tbsp @oil{3%tbsp}, 1 tsp @smoked paprika{2%tsp} and 1 tsp ground @cumin{2%tsp}. Give everything a good mix so that all the chunks are coated in spices, season with salt and @pepper{1}, then roast for ~{25%min}s until cooked.

Meanwhile, heat the remaining oil in a large saucepan over a medium heat. Add the @onion{1}, carrot and @celery{2}. Cook for ~{8-10%min}s, stirring occasionally until soft, then crush in the @garlic{2%clove} and cook for ~{1%min} more. Add the remaining @dried{1%tsp} spices and @tomato purée{1%tbsp}. Give everything a good mix and cook for ~{1%min} more.

Add the red pepper, @chopped tomatoes{201%g} and 200ml water. Bring the @chilli{1.5%tsp} to a boil, then simmer for ~{20%min}s. Tip in the @beans{400%g} and cook for another ~{10%min}s before adding the sweet potato. Season to taste then serve with @lime wedges{}, guacamole, rice and coriander. Will keep, in an airtight container in the freezer, for up to three months. To make in a slow cooker Heat the oil in a large frying pan over a medium heat. Add the onion, carrot and celery. Cook for ~{8-10%min}s, stirring occasionally until soft, then crush in the garlic, tip in the sweet potato chunks and cook for ~{1%min} more. Add all the dried spices, oregano and tomato purée, cook for ~{1%min}, then tip into a slow cooker. Add the red pepper and chopped tomatoes. Give everything a good stir then cook on low for 5 hrs. Stir in the @beans{400%g} and cook for another ~{30%min}s to 1 hr. Season to taste and serve with lime wedges, guacamole, rice and coriander.
